**`approve_review` has no authentication/authorization model**: The `contributor_uuid` is taken directly from the MCP client request. Any client can approve a review as any contributor -- there is no verification that the caller is actually the contributor they claim to be. In a multi-user context, this means any MCP client can forge approvals. At minimum, the server should identify the current user (e.g., from git config) and either enforce that approvals are from that user, or clearly document that this is a trust-the-client design.